{
  "texts": [
    "Time series anomaly detection (AD) is ubiquitous for web systems [9,11,13,14,17,21,33,36,49,50].",
    "Numerous web systems, such as online advertising systems, are monitored using a vast array of time series data (e.g., conversion rate) [52].",
    "Deploying time series AD algorithms is essential for timely detecting anomalies and initiating subsequent diagnosis and remediation processes.Anomalies are rare in real-world time series data [41], making it difficult to label them and train a supervised model for anomaly detection [50].",
    "Instead, unsupervised machine learning techniques are commonly used [5,7,16,18,27,34,50,54,[57][58][59].",
    "These techniques can be divided into two categories: prediction-based [16,18,59] and construction-based [5,27,34,50,54]."
  ]
}